title: S. Jersey Boys: S.J. boys: Washington Twp. edges Cherokee, 1-0, for 12th straight win
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports With only four minutes remaining in regulation, sophomore Clayton Cross dribbled the ball along the Cherokee end line and sent a cross to senior midfielder George Charalabidis, who knocked the ball into the right corner from 12 yards out.
The Minutemen (12-0-1) have won 12 straight games since a 1-1 draw with Cherokee in the season opener on Sept. 11. They have remained humble throughout the streak, Snyder said. 
"They understand that anything can happen on any day," he said. 
In another Olympic Conference game, Cody Cassise and Zach Malcolm each netted two goals, and Seneca rolled by host Winslow Township, 5-0. The duo also combined for three assists. 
Coaches Tournament. Ishmael Boakai scored with 12 minutes left and No. 9 Cherry Hill West defeated No. 10 Shawnee, 1-0, in a first-round matchup. Andrew Robertson made seven saves. 
Burlington County League. Pat McCarthy scored in the second half on a pass from Jarrod Averill to give visiting Cinnaminson a 1-0 win over No. 6 Burlington Township. 
Francis Kanu scored two goals, and host Burlington City rallied to defeat Westampton Tech, 4-3. Brandon Alvarenga and Osman Cakir also scored. 
Connor Reilly scored twice to lead Holy Cross to a 3-0 victory at Maple Shade. Pat Harkansan also scored. 
A hat trick from Hunter Swanson led the way for Florence in a 6-0 victory at Medford Tech. Hamza Er, Nick Hazel, and Sefa Ocak also scored. 
Kevin Robinson made four saves for Delran in a 5-1 win at Northern Burlington. Skylar Diggs, Brandon Kendall, Louie Nocito, Ryan Strauss, and Mike Strohlein each scored a goal. 
Ryan Carducci recorded a hat trick in Palmyra's 7-0 victory over visiting Willingboro. 
Colonial Conference. Sam Bealor and Matt Fell each scored two goals in the second half, and No. 4 Haddonfield defeated host Audubon, 4-0. 
Jake Roselle led the charge for visiting Haddon Heights, scoring two goals in a 3-1 win over Lindenwold. Nick Mosko also scored. 
Will Eagan netted two goals for Collingswood in a 5-0 victory against visiting Overbrook. Osmund Berrie, Rajorn Elliott, and Kevin Walters also scored. 
Cape-Atlantic League. Joe Fala had a hat trick for host Middle Township, including the winner with five minutes remaining, in a 4-3 win over Pleasantville.
